review_blob: Aroma is nice and fruity, not skunk a dunk. The head is super foamy, like a foam dome of monk home. Very pretty beer, the color is pleasing to the eye, much like the happy amber morn. Palatable and charming, Thanks.

A surprising find at the local liquor store, hidden among the common swill that the yokels here imbibe. Delicious! The richness of the flavors makes for a very good Saturday night beer. Not too heavy on the palate, goes down remarkably smooth.

It has kind of an odd smell, unusual but not wholly unpleasant. The taste is a lot like how it smells but then subsides to a peaceful, and mellow aftertaste. Its sweet, but I cannot quite put my finger on what it smells and tastes like. ?
Pours nice and pretty, but head dissipates quite quickly. Definitely has a very faint pumpkin taste and feels very "autumn-ish", not too bad!
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale
